==English==

===Etymology===

:Named after the French phyicist André-Marie Ampère.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''ampere''' ''or'' (''old-fashioned'') '''ampère''' (''plural'' '''amperes''')
#In the [[International System of Units]], the [[base unit]] of electrical [[current]]; the current which, if maintained in two straight [[parallel]] [[conductor]]s of [[infinite]] length, of negligible circular [[cross-section]], and placed 1 [[metre]] apart in a [[vacuum]], would produce between these conductors a [[force]] equal to 2 &times; 10<sup>-7</sup> [[newton]]s per metre of length.  Symbol: A
#: ''This battery can deliver a peak current of 5 '''amperes'''.''

====Short form====
'''amp'''

